I designed a production-grade Kubernetes architecture using Amazon Elastic Kubernetes Service (EKS) focused on High Availability, Scalability, Security, and Observability.

ðŸ”¹ High Availability
 Deployed EKS in a multi-AZ Amazon VPC with worker nodes running in private subnets across multiple availability zones, ensuring no single point of failure. Traffic is distributed through an Application Load Balancer for resilient cross-AZ routing.

ðŸ”¹ Scalability
 Implemented Horizontal Pod Autoscaler for application scaling and integrated Cluster Autoscaler with Amazon EC2 Auto Scaling to dynamically scale worker nodes during traffic spikes and burst workloads.

